text:
Approval of the document on prevention of crimes and violations in the field of capital market

With the adoption of the document on prevention of crimes and violations in the field of capital market in the High Council of Exchange, the serious focus and priority of the stock exchange organization was to promote market health.
01 Nov 2019, 12:30 by Bulletin News | bultannews.com
According to the Bulletin News, Jaafar Jamali pointed to the approval and approval of the "Capital Markets Crime Prevention Document" at a recent meeting of the High Council of Stock Exchange: With the approval of this document in the High Council, the focus and priority The seriousness of the stock exchange will be on preventing and promoting the health of the capital market and promoting the health and transparency of the capital market.
He said the document had been submitted for implementation over a three-year period and that the organization would focus on preventing capital market anomalies.
Jamali stated that the document was drafted and implemented by the initiative of the Department of Prevention and Promotion of Capital Market Health. The opinion of the capital market regulators and regulators was finalized and approved by the High Council of Exchange and Securities after the due process.
He continued: "The document on prevention of offenses and violations in the field of capital market" is a collective treaty on the prevention of offenses and offenses and, as mentioned in the document, with the participation of all regulatory and executive units of the organization, market elements. Capital and all self-regulated organizations will be implemented. According to the document, health capital and transparency of the capital market will be pursued and achieved through cooperation and interaction of all stakeholders.
The document, which aims to promote the health and health of the capital market business environment and eliminate the areas of capital market offenses and offenses, as well as maintaining capital market order, Implementation of criminal and non-criminal prevention strategies with the priority of non-criminal prevention, including situational and social prevention, has been developed; it has a process and strategy that will encompass a range of preventive strategic measures.
He added: Reducing the incentives to commit crimes, reducing the scope, tools and opportunities to commit crimes, increasing the security and desirability of domestic and foreign investment in markets and related fields, and gaining public confidence in the capital market, transparency and upgrading conditions. Investing through education and culture, expanding financial literacy, general and legal knowledge of market participants, promoting the health and hygiene of the capital market business environment are expected outcomes and applications of the document.
At the end of the day, the Deputy Director of the Stock Exchange announced the serious determination of the Organization to prevent and promote the health of the capital market with the participation of all supervisory and executive units of the organization, the pillars of this market and all its organizations.
It should be noted that the document requires the achievement of the document's expected goals and outcomes, the cooperation and constructive engagement of all relevant parties through the implementation of the following processes and strategies:
۱. Providing reporting patterns and collecting statistics and information for all areas (including transactions, licenses, correspondence, oversight, meetings, complaints, violations, offenses, information on market participants, investors, etc.) in Capital markets and their continuous updating for scientific analysis of statistics, the etiology of offenses, anomalies and prioritization to investigate;
۲. Establishing and strengthening the surveillance and early detection system of capital market failures to identify market abnormalities and bottlenecks;
Continuous monitoring and review of laws and regulations (including guidelines, bylaws, style sheets, etc.);
۴. Reviewing, monitoring and adapting the processes in the capital market to laws and regulations, reforming current forms and procedures, and adopting new regulations to improve processes;
۵. Optimizing the regulatory process to prevent conflict of laws and regulations, facilitating and expediting the regulatory and regulatory process and improving regulatory quality;
۶. Technical prevention through information technology enhancement, systems development, and process electronics;
۷. Organize, integrate, and improve processes related to licensing;
۸. Creating free access to information for transparency and protection of citizenship in accordance with laws and regulations;
۹. Institutionalize the communication of the organs of the organization on various issues through the creation of relevant specialized working groups;
۱۰. Creating prevention circuits in the organization's subsidiaries and self-regulated organizations and strengthening, developing and supporting them;
۱۱. Reviewing processes related to dispute resolution and reconciliation to facilitate and expedite adjudication;
۱۲. Creation and updating of the Bank of Capital Market rules and regulations for the purpose of ease of access and public use;
۱۳. Culture, public orientation, and effective advertising to promote the level of financial literacy, public knowledge, and legal knowledge of capital market participants;
۱۴. Facilitate the operation and simplification of laws and regulations for the general public by providing behavioral patterns relevant to each category of capital market players (publishers, financial managers, investors, etc.) and deepening specialized training through the provision of educational content and Its inclusion in the educational system as well as monitoring of educational content;
۱۵. Use incentive mechanisms to detect public anomalies, offenses and offenses in the capital market;
۱۶. Strengthening and expanding the use of consultation and collective wisdom;
۱۷. Use of restorative justice and judicial mediation practices in legal terms;
۱۸. Pursue the necessary measures to strengthen effective judicial decisions in the capital market;
۱۹. Implementation of situational prevention strategies in line with the objectives of the law promoting the health of the administrative system and combating corruption;
۲۰. Promote violations handling and continuous improvement of processes and mechanisms for detecting, investigating, and prosecuting capital market crimes.
To execute the document of specialized committees such as the "General Committee for the Prevention of Offenses and its Offenses and its Workgroups", the "Implementation Committee and its Committees", the "Cyberspace High Commission", the "Citizens Rights Protection Committee, Free Access To public information and education. "
